From 36a63c5f8b3018793ddcf4e96aede35e6ea556a4 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Marcus Figueiredo <figueiredo@protonmail.com>
Date: Tue, 23 Jun 2026 17:07:59 -0300
Subject: [PATCH 3/5] host: add Metal-backed Vulkan-only build support for
 macOS

Introduces the macOS/darwin build target: a CAMetalLayer-based native
sub-window (native_sub_window_metal.mm, replacing the deprecated
NSOpenGL/cocoa path for the Vulkan-only configuration), the darwin
framework/link-args block in meson.build (CoreFoundation, IOKit,
AppKit, Foundation, Metal, QuartzCore), and GFXSTREAM_ENABLE_HOST_GLES
guards across frame_buffer.cpp/color_buffer.cpp/gles_compat.h so the
GL-emulation-only code paths compile out cleanly when only the Vulkan
decoder is enabled. Also adds stub backends (iostream, snapshot) for
build configurations that don't need those subsystems on this
platform.

This is what first made gfxstream buildable for macOS/HVF at all,
predating the gpu-gfxstream session work in libkrun. Hand-extracted by
diffing the vendored gfxstream tree (with the two later GLES-decoder
patches reverse-applied) against this branch.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Sonnet 4.6 <noreply@anthropic.com>
Signed-off-by: Marcus Figueiredo <figueiredo@protonmail.com>
